{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17487291","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17487291"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:04:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:04:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"311"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"311","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/311"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.49,0.17,0.13,0.09,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"311"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92401"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"311","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/311"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"311"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75720"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"1984"},{"type":"tags","id":"4847"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4979"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11639"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"31587"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31588"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42053"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92401","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/92401"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 62-year-old man presents to a rural hospital with a three day history of drowsiness, lethargy, anorexia, nausea and vomiting. He is not able to give a clear history and his wife states that he has recently been diagnosed with metastatic lung cancer. He is confused, dehydrated and unable to state where he is.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHis blood pressure is 110/80mmHg, pulse 90/min and temperature 37.2\u003Csup\u003Eo\u003C/sup\u003EC. An ECG tracing shows a short QT interval and widened T waves. His serum calcium is 3.50 mmol/L (2.10 - 2.55). The patient has enjoyed relatively good health until the last few days and he is for full treatment measures. An intravenous line is inserted and fluid replacement started with isotonic saline.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pamidronate","Cinacalcet","Haemodialysis","Furosemide","Denosumab"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has obvious symptomatic hypercalcaemia: abdominal pain, confusion and ECG changes; likely caused by PTHrP-producing lung malignancy. He is noted to have full measures on his treatment plan and thus all treatment options will be pursued. The order of management is rehydration with normal saline which has already begun then\u00a0bisphosphonates\u00a0(eg \u003Cstrong\u003Epamidronate\u003C/strong\u003E or zoledronic acid) to lower the calcium. Dialysis is used for resistant, life-threatening cases and would be indicated if bisphosphonates were not effective in this case. Cinacalcet is a calcimimetic agent for parathyroid induced hypercalcaemia. Furosemide increases renal excretion of calcium but can dehydrate the patient initially, thereby increasing the calcium concentration and thus should only be given once the patient is fluid-resuscitated. Denosumab is used for hypercalcaemia that does not respond to bisphosphonates or if they contraindcated due to severe renal impairment.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A bisphosphonate is first-line treatment for hypercalcaemia related to malignancy."],"references":["Zagzag J, Hu MI, Fisher SB, et al. Hypercalcemia and Cancer: Differential Diagnosis and Treatment. Ca Cancer J Clin 2018; 68:377-86."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75720"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"311"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75720","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/75720"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-17T16:31:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-17T16:31:36+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"311"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92401"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"78","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/78"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level III","synonyms":null,"description":"Apply, analyze, evaluate, and create (implementing, organizing, and critiqui